      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2007_Problems_2007_page_001_2",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A–2 Find the least possible area of a convex set in the plane that intersects both branches of the hyperbola xy = 1 and both branches of the hyperbola xy = −1. (A set S in the plane is called convex if for any two points in S the line segment connecting them is contained in S.)",
        "bbox": [
          0.09333333333333334,
          0.17454545454545456,
          0.4894117647058824,
          0.24727272727272728
        ],
        "order": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2007_Problems_2007_page_001_3",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A-3 Let k be a positive integer. Suppose that the integers 1, 2, 3, ..., 3k + 1 are written down in random order. What is the probability that at no time during this pro- cess, the sum of the integers that have been written up to that time is a positive integer divisible by 3? Your answer should be in closed form, but may include fac- torials.",
        "bbox": [
          0.09333333333333334,
          0.25636363636363635,
          0.49019607843137253,
          0.35818181818181816
        ],
        "order": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2007_Problems_2007_page_001_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B−3 Let x0 = 1 and for n ≥ 0, 1et xn+1 = 3xn + |xn √5. In particular, x1 = 5, x2 = 26, x3 = 136, x4 = 712. Find a closed-form expression for x2oo7. (a means the largest integer ≤ a.)",
        "bbox": [
          0.5231372549019608,
          0.2684848484848485,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.3278787878787879
        ],
        "order": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2007_Problems_2007_page_001_11",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B–4 Let n be a positive integer. Find the number of pairs P, Q of polynomials with real coefficients such that",
        "bbox": [
          0.523921568627451,
          0.33636363636363636,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.36666666666666664
        ],
        "order": 8
